commentary: Rahmat Shah to Sabbir Rahman, OUT the party is over. Sabbir has thrown it away, and so Rahmat has the last laugh. Credit to the bowler, who wasn't afraid to toss the ball up despite being hit for a six. Sabbir once again went for a big heave, but was beaten by the drift and turn as he managed to top edge the slog straight to short third man. End of an excellent partnership. Afghanistan's reaction seemed to suggest they were relieved, and not elated

commentary: Mosharraf Hossain to Nawroz Mangal, OUT it can't get more plumb than that, the comeback man has a wicket, and it is a big one too! He shapes to play a sweep across the line, but the ball was pushed through quickly and it kept coming back in to hit him flush on the pad. That would have crashed into middle. Mangal knew he was trapped the moment the ball hit the pad. The umpire didn't take long to raise the finger either. All the elements of a typical left-arm spinner's wicket there. Drift, the angle and a hint of turn. So lovely to watch.

commentary: Taskin Ahmed to Rahmat Shah, OUT the short ball has sucker punched Rahmat, who was peppered with yorkers. This one was dug in short outside off, Rahmat looks to pull - made it look like he was playing a cross court forehand - but the ball got big on him to take the top edge that was easily pouched at midwicket. Rahmat's feet were off the ground when he made contact with that ball. With positions like those, you're unlikely to be in control of too many short deliveries. More so in this case as he had to fetch it from way outside off.

commentary: Mosaddek Hossain to Rashid Khan, OUT pitched up outside off and gets forward and taps it to point. They take off for a quick single though it goes directly to him. Direct hit at the non-striker's end and the umpire takes a long time before deciding to go upstairs. Looks like he is safe initially, but replays show that he out of his crease by more than a mile. Direct hits are always close and this one showed why. The third umpire presses the wrong button and the crowd is stunned momentarily but the big screen flashes the right decision eventually

commentary: Mosaddek Hossain to Najibullah Zadran, OUT both halves of the partnership have now been dismissed. It was floated up and on off, tempted him to go for a big drive and that is exactly what the batsman does, only that he gets a big outside edge that is snaffled at first slip. Bangladesh one wicket away from their 100th ODI win
